
// This Hyperlambda code checks if a node named "cascading" exists within the [.arguments] node and is not null. It then verifies if the value of this "cascading" node is exactly "true". The [and] slot ensures that all these conditions must be true for the entire expression to evaluate to true.
and
   exists:x:@.arguments/*/cascading
   not-null:x:@.arguments/*/cascading
   eq
      get-value:x:@.arguments/*/cascading
      .:bool:true
